27:09.355 --> 27:14.682
He says that our suffering is not worth comparing to the glory that is going to be revealed in us.

27:17.566 --> 27:22.994
And he says that when we suffer, it doesn't mean that God is displeased with us or that he's distant from us.

27:23.842 --> 27:24.783
Christ suffered.

27:28.148 --> 27:38.303
And at the end he concludes, he says, and we know that in all things God works for the good of those who love him, who were called according to his purpose.

27:43.050 --> 27:53.746
So having talked about these things and having talked about being called, about being justified before God, about being glorified,

27:55.298 --> 27:57.000
Scripture then says these words.

27:57.961 --> 28:01.085
What then shall we say in response to these things?

28:03.609 --> 28:06.793
Just recap, these are the things that it's saying that about.

28:06.913 --> 28:23.314
What then shall we say in response to these things that there is no condemnation for us, that we have the Holy Spirit living in us, that we are children, not slaves, that the Spirit

28:23.522 --> 28:36.241
Testifies to this, tells us it's true that we are God's children, that God is working all things for our good, and that we are being conformed to the image of the Son of Jesus.

28:36.641 --> 28:39.666
What then shall we say in response to these things?

28:41.549 --> 28:45.074
If God is for us, who can be against us?

28:48.162 --> 28:52.026
He who did not spare his own son, but gave him up for us all.

28:52.106 --> 28:57.412
How will he not also, along with him, graciously give us all things?

28:59.935 --> 29:01.677
If God is for us, who can be against us?

29:06.422 --> 29:07.504
Can the leaders of Iran?

29:10.987 --> 29:13.330
If God is for us, who can be against us?

29:17.954 --> 29:19.095
Did you hear the second bit?

29:21.578 --> 29:25.082
He who did not spare his own son, but gave him up for us all.

29:25.142 --> 29:29.627
How will he not also, along with him, graciously give us all things?

29:30.347 --> 29:37.715
Everything that we need for our improvement, everything that we need to be conformed to the son, is God going to hold it back from us?

29:38.396 --> 29:39.417
He gave us his son.

29:40.899 --> 29:42.420
Is he going to hold anything back from us?

29:45.864 --> 29:47.666
We are the forgiven.

29:47.778 --> 29:49.320
free children of God.

29:50.522 --> 29:53.105
He is for us who can be against us.

29:57.211 --> 30:02.358
It goes on to say, who will bring any charge against those whom God has chosen?

30:02.579 --> 30:04.581
It is God who justifies.

30:05.703 --> 30:07.405
Who then is the one who condemns?

30:08.326 --> 30:08.767
No one.

30:10.389 --> 30:16.658
We have here the image of a courtroom or of a king and his court.

30:17.634 --> 30:28.565
If the creator and ruler of the universe of everything has said you are justified, you are forgiven, who can argue with that?

30:31.528 --> 30:32.349
Who can condemn us?

30:36.273 --> 30:44.722
If we had worked for it, if we had made that claim that we're all right, that we're righteous, then someone could

30:45.314 --> 30:48.178
argue with us, someone could dispute it, someone could condemn us.

30:48.679 --> 30:52.384
But if God has said it, who can argue with him?

30:59.274 --> 31:01.438
The next verse, Christ Jesus who died.

31:02.419 --> 31:10.211
More than that, who was raised to life is at the right hand of God and is also interceding for us.

31:10.751 --> 31:12.594
We have the spirit interceding for us.

31:12.994 --> 31:18.320
We have Christ Jesus raised from the dead, interceding from us.

31:18.880 --> 31:33.877
So we've gone from the courtroom, from the ruler, who has declared us righteous, to our great high priest, who is interceding for us every moment of every day that we live, interceding for us before the Father.

31:39.823 --> 31:42.386
Who shall separate us from the love of Christ?

31:45.250 --> 31:48.695
Who shall separate us from the love of Christ?

31:50.317 --> 32:02.413
Shall trouble or hardship or persecution or famine or nakedness or danger or sword?

32:07.360 --> 32:12.687
Now in all these things we are more than conquerors through him who loved us.

32:14.649 --> 32:15.090
Some

32:15.330 --> 32:18.114
Translations say we are super-conquerous.

32:20.497 --> 32:21.719
You see those list of things.

32:23.321 --> 32:26.526
They can't hope to separate us from the love of Christ.

32:29.090 --> 32:35.078
Danger, sword, persecution, famine, nakedness, trouble, hardship.

32:36.460 --> 32:38.543
They can't separate us from the love of Christ.

32:39.344 --> 32:43.570
We are super-conquerous through Him who loved us.

32:50.274 --> 32:58.602
Is this enough to encourage us to give us assurance in God's work?

33:00.644 --> 33:06.329
Shall we still look to ourselves, to our own righteousness, to our own works?

33:10.093 --> 33:12.115
Should we believe any lies of the enemy?

33:16.719 --> 33:19.762
We are more than conquerors through Him who loved us.

33:20.834 --> 33:28.303
If you find yourself doubting your position before God, your eternity with him.

33:30.225 --> 33:40.898
If the enemy is lying to you and trying to condemn you, remember these words, the last words of Romans 8.

33:42.560 --> 33:50.610
For I am convinced that neither death nor life, neither angels nor demons,

33:51.458 --> 33:55.864
Neither the present nor the future nor any powers.

33:56.885 --> 34:00.711
Neither height nor depth nor anything else in all creation.

34:02.333 --> 34:07.900
We'll be able to separate us from the love of God in Christ Jesus our Lord.

34:12.086 --> 34:17.874
For I am convinced that neither death nor life, neither angels nor demons,

34:18.242 --> 34:32.078
Neither the present nor the future, nor any powers, neither height nor depth nor anything else in all creation will be able to separate us from the love of God in Christ Jesus, our Lord.

34:36.283 --> 34:42.410
You see, we know what we have been saved from, slavery to sin, the wages of sin which are death.

34:44.753 --> 34:45.874
But from a place

34:46.114 --> 34:51.722
of security, we can marvel with joy about what we have been saved to.

34:51.762 --> 35:00.373
Adoption as sons and daughters of the Most High God, fellowship with one another.

35:00.413 --> 35:08.064
To be a people who have the Holy Spirit in them, comforting, guiding, correcting.

35:10.207 --> 35:15.634
But in these last few verses, we are reminded that it is God's perfect love for us.

35:16.226 --> 35:19.389
that is our new reality, that is our eternity.

35:20.390 --> 35:24.735
Perfect love, perfectly known, perfectly loved.

35:25.916 --> 35:29.660
A love that keeps us, sustains us, surrounds us.

35:31.302 --> 35:40.332
It makes our eternity not just a relief, but a joy, eternally satisfying.

35:42.514 --> 35:46.098
And confident in our salvation, we go on with the mindset that

35:47.618 --> 35:49.020
Okay, God, you've got more for me.

35:49.501 --> 35:49.961
What is it?

35:51.003 --> 35:51.463
It's good.

35:52.705 --> 35:55.169
What good things do you have in store for me?

35:58.553 --> 36:09.388
This isn't about giving us license to do nothing or to just sit placidly in what Christ has done for us.

36:10.410 --> 36:12.292
This is about where we start from.

36:13.554 --> 36:16.338
This is about the position we live out of

36:17.570 --> 36:19.532
One of assurance, not fear.

36:20.673 --> 36:23.176
One of trusting God, not ourselves.

36:25.098 --> 36:29.783
And from that place, living to bring glory to the one who saved us.

36:33.146 --> 36:44.818
Lord, I pray that you would open the eyes of our hearts, that we would know the love that you have for us, that we would know your love like strong arms holding us from now until eternity.

36:47.202 --> 36:52.907
that we would have confidence, security, and assurance in your work in what you have done.

36:54.909 --> 36:58.092
And that we would be a people that speak life to those around us.

36:59.334 --> 37:01.976
To your glory, in Jesus' name, I pray.

37:02.817 --> 37:02.937
Amen.

37:05.219 --> 37:06.761
We've come to the end of this week's message.

37:07.361 --> 37:08.963
We hope you've been impacted and inspired.

37:09.823 --> 37:16.690
Please keep up to date with everything that's happening by visiting our website at www.livechurchdorrington.com.

